@doll agenda poem #1, hastily scrawled at 2 am because I got distracted recreating Bach's Little Fugue in G Minor on FL Studio:

*A single pitch to split the dark of loss,
not held as memoir, fear, nor high regard
but snaring, sharp and crystalline riposte;
we honor souls erased and psyche-scarred.

Panoptic light, immortal by design
and penned in scheme to spite omnipotence,
our ignorance, our vitae, uncombine.
In tandem force we stay the pestilence.

Oh chord recurred, oh patron of despair
for fleeting fear of times now long since borne,
that shell once Yours entombed in disrepair;
Your epitaph engraved in sweetest scorn.

The river sings, and You, in kind;
The Aeons pale beneath your mind.*
